President Muhammadu Buhari Monday launched the Presidential Youth Empowerment Scheme (P-YES) at the State House Abuja. P-YES, an intervention programme of the Buhari administration, is aimed at creating 774,000 jobs across the Local Government Areas (LGAs) in the country. Present at the launch were Vice President Yemi Osinbajo, Senate President Ahmed Lawan, Kano Governor Abdullahi Ganduje, Ebonyi Governor Dave Umahi and other top government officials. Here are images of the event.           